sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant FE as React Frontend
    participant API as FastAPI
    participant Graph as LangGraph Pipeline
    participant Groq as Groq LLM
    participant JobSpy as python-jobspy
    participant PW as Playwright
    participant DB as SQLite

    User->>FE: Fill resume path + settings<br/>Click "Start Run"
    FE->>API: POST /api/run {resume_path, dry_run, settings}
    API-->>FE: 200 { status: "started" }
    API->>Graph: asyncio.create_task(run_pipeline(...))

    Note over Graph: NODE 1 — parse_resume
    Graph->>Graph: Read file (pdfplumber/docx/md)
    Graph->>Groq: RESUME_PARSE_PROMPT + resume_text
    Groq-->>Graph: JSON → ParsedResume

    Note over Graph: NODE 2 — generate_queries
    Graph->>Groq: QUERY_GENERATOR_PROMPT + roles/skills
    Groq-->>Graph: list[str] search_queries

    Note over Graph: NODE 3 — search_jobs (parallel)
    par LinkedIn × queries
        Graph->>JobSpy: search(query, location, job_type)
        JobSpy-->>Graph: list[Job]
    and Internshala × queries
        Graph->>JobSpy: search(query, location, job_type)
        JobSpy-->>Graph: list[Job]
    and Naukri × queries
        Graph->>JobSpy: search(query, location, job_type)
        JobSpy-->>Graph: list[Job]
    and Wellfound × queries
        Graph->>JobSpy: search(query, location, job_type)
        JobSpy-->>Graph: list[Job]
    end
    Graph->>Graph: Merge → jobs_found[]

    Note over Graph: NODE 4 — rank_jobs (asyncio.gather)
    loop For each job in parallel
        Graph->>Groq: JOB_RANK_PROMPT + skills + job_description
        Groq-->>Graph: {relevance_score, matched_skills, missing_skills}
    end
    Graph->>Graph: Filter score >= 0.6, sort desc, cap at MAX_APPLICATIONS

    Note over Graph: LOOP — per job
    loop For each job in jobs_filtered
        Graph->>Graph: process_next_job (index++)

        Note over Graph: NODE 6 — tailor_resume
        Graph->>Groq: RESUME_TAILOR_PROMPT + job + resume_json
        Groq-->>Graph: TailoredResume (summary, skills, projects reordered)

        Note over Graph: NODE 7 — apply_job
        Graph->>PW: launch_browser → login → navigate to job URL
        PW->>PW: Fill application form
        PW-->>Graph: ApplicationResult (applied/failed/skipped)
        Graph->>Graph: generate PDF + DOCX (WeasyPrint + python-docx)

        Note over Graph: NODE 8 — save_application
        Graph->>DB: INSERT INTO applications (...)
        DB-->>Graph: OK
        Graph->>DB: Save checkpoint (AsyncSqliteSaver)
    end

    Note over Graph: NODE 9 — print_summary
    Graph->>Graph: Log applied/skipped/failed counts

    User->>FE: Navigate to Status page
    FE->>API: GET /api/status
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM applications
    DB-->>API: rows
    API-->>FE: list[ApplicationOut]
    FE-->>User: Table with status badges + scores
